Step 1: Calculate the Quick Assets (cash, bank deposits, interest receivable, and accounts receivable) at period end.
 • Cash on Hand = 145666.48  
 • Bank Deposits = 194711.58  
 • Interest Receivable = 1731.44  
 • Accounts Receivable = 3558301.64  

Sum of Quick Assets = 145666.48 + 194711.58 + 1731.44 + 3558301.64 = 3900411.14

Step 2: From the balance sheet, the Total Current Liabilities at period end = 3054996.05

Step 3: Compute the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
 = 3900411.14 / 3054996.05 ≈ 1.28

Step 4: Determine the Net Profit from the income statement:
 Net Profit = -1175062.19  
Total Revenue = 7099920.95

Step 5: Compute the Net Profit Margin:
 Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
 = (-1175062.19 / 7099920.95) × 100 ≈ -16.57%

Therefore, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "1.28",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-16.57%"
  }
}
